<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She often showcases her stunning sense of style with her work ensembles. </p>

<p>And Ashley Roberts looked effortlessly cool in a casual monochrome ensemble as she exited London's Global studios after presenting her Heart FM show on Monday. </p>

<p>The Pussycat Dolls star, 39, donned a plunging white top beneath a black bomber jacket and matching joggers as she made her way down the street.</p>

<p>Style: Ashley Roberts looked effortlessly cool in a casual monochrome ensemble as she exited London's Global studios after presenting her Heart FM show on Monday</p>

<p>Adding to her stylish look, Ashley draped a black and silver handbag across her body, while she donned a quirky pair of black cat eye sunglasses. </p>

<p>While she completed her laid back ensemble with a chunky pair of white trainers. </p>

<p>The React singer kept her blonde tresses loose for the day, while she let her natural beauty shine through with a minimal make-up palette. </p>

<p>Ashley, who celebrated her 39th birthday this month, appeared in great spirits as she walked, flashing a dazzling smile. </p>

<p>Looking good: The Pussycat Dolls star, 39, donned a plunging white top beneath a black bomber jacket and matching joggers as she made her way down the street</p>

<p>The media personality recently revealed she is open to the idea of adopting a child in the future.</p>

<p>Speaking in an interview with Fabulous magazine in July, she said: 'I'm definitely open to the idea of adoption.</p>

<p>'You just never know what the future is going to bring and the most important thing is to be happy and, whether my body naturally has kids or not, we'll see what life brings. I'm definitely open to that.'</p>

<p>Details: Adding to her stylish look, Ashley draped a black and silver handbag across her body, while she donned a quirky pair of black cat eye sunglasses</p>

<p>Fashionista: The React singer kept her blonde tresses loose for the day, while she let her natural beauty shine through with a minimal make-up palette</p>

<p>The blonde also reflected on dating following her split from Italian Strictly Come Dancing professional Giovanni Pernice, 29.</p>

<p>They called time on their year-long romance in January after meeting during Ashley's stint on the BBC One dance competition in late 2018.</p>

<p>The TV star said: 'I'm good on my own, though. I'm pretty independent. It's nice to have that connection with someone, but at the moment lockdown is still [effectively] here, so "me" is where it is.'</p>

<p>In good company: The blonde celebrated her 39th birthday in style with her nearest and dearest earlier this month</p>
